results.name: Expansion of q^(-5/3) * c(q^2)^3 / (9 * c(q)) in powers of q where c() is a cubic AGM theta function.
comment: Cubic AGM theta functions: a(q) (see A004016), b(q) (A005928), c(q) (A005882).
link: G. C. Greubel, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..2500
formula: Expansion of q^(-5/3) * eta(q) * eta(q^6)^9 / (eta(q^2) * eta(q^3))^3 in powers of q.
a(n) = 1/6 * b(3*n + 5) where b() is multiplicative with b(2^e) = 2 - 2^e, b(3^e) = 0^e, b(p^e) = (p^(e+1) - 1) / (p - 1) if p>3.
mathematica: a[ n_] := SeriesCoefficient[ QPochhammer[ x] QPochhammer[ x^6]^9 / (QPochhammer[ x^2] QPochhammer[ x^3])^3, {x, 0, n}];
a[ n_] := SeriesCoefficient[ (QPochhammer[ -x^3] QPochhammer[ x^12])^3 / (QPochhammer[ -x] QPochhammer[ x^4]), {x, 0, n}];
program: (PARI) {a(n) = my(A); if( n<0, 0, A = x * O(x^n); polcoeff( eta(x + A) * eta(x^6 + A)^9 / (eta(x^2 + A) * eta(x^3 + A))^3, n))};
